cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses a supervised learning method for neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also compares the proposed method with other existing methods such as extreme learning machine, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of Moore-Penrose approximation, which is a common technique in linear algebra and optimization, and hence the paper could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of the proposed method for image classification, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the proposed method for control systems, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
